Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.15,0:00:29.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs130\bord0\pos(950,950)\b0\fsp0.4}地         球         脉         动 {\fsp0.5}  I I
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.84,0:00:39.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想象一个世界\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Imagine a world
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.59,0:00:43.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,气温高达50摄氏度\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}where temperatures rise to 50 degrees Centigrade.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.34,0:00:53.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有什么能阻挡烈日  狂风与沙尘\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Where there's no escape from sun, wind and dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.95,0:01:03.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想象一个世界  几乎没有食物和水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Imagine a world with almost no food or water.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.21,0:01:15.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这种地方占据了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These are the conditions
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.07,0:01:18.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,地球上三分之一的土地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}in one third of the lands of our planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.16,0:01:27.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,生长于斯  必须掌握非凡的生存策略\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}To live here demands the most extraordinary survival strategies.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.00,0:01:38.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1000,1000)\fs140\bord0\b0\pos(960,1000)\1c&H2264FF&}沙        漠
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.38,0:01:55.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(960,1440)}这是世界上最古老的沙漠\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is the oldest desert in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.75,0:01:57.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs60\fsp5\fad(1000,1000)\pos(960,1100)\bord0\b0}画 外 音\N{\fs90}大卫 · 爱登堡   爵士
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.79,0:01:58.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(960,1440)}纳米布沙漠  位于非洲西南部\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The Namib in south-west Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.02,0:02:03.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,干旱已经持续了五千五百万年\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's been dry for 55 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.02,0:02:13.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对于捕食者来说  生活异常艰难\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Life here for a hunter is as hard as it gets.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.27,0:02:26.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一群狮子\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A pride of lions.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.75,0:02:29.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她们是极少数能够忍受如此\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}One of the very few that endures this desert's
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.98,0:02:33.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,高温缺水的沙漠环境的物种之一\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}scorching temperatures and lack of water.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.15,0:02:54.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沙漠狩猎有着特殊的难题\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Hunting here presents special problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.35,0:03:02.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这群直角大羚羊\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A herd of oryx,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.43,0:03:06.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是方圆三十二公里内唯一的猎物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the only prey within 20 miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.82,0:03:14.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里没有任何伏击可用的遮挡物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Out here, there is no cover for an ambush.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.84,0:03:17.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,唯有直截了当扑杀过去\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It'll have to be a straight chase.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.26,0:03:57.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她们失败了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They have failed
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.27,0:04:02.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每失败一次  狮群离饿死就更近一步\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and each failed hunt brings the lions closer to starvation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.27,0:04:16.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为了寻找食物充饥\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}To find enough to eat,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.37,0:04:22.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,狮群不断地在瑞士国境那么大的区域内搜寻\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the pride continually searches an area the size of Switzerland.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.96,0:04:38.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,三天里它们走了一百六十一公里  仍然一无所获\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Three days and 100 miles later, and still no kill.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.78,0:04:43.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是濒临绝望的时刻\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These are desperate times.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.38,0:04:50.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她们领土的边缘有一条干涸的河床\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A dry riverbed on the edge of their territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.06,0:04:56.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,长颈鹿是附近唯一的动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The only animals here are giraffe,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.45,0:05:02.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但这重达一吨的巨兽一脚就能踢死一头狮子\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but these one-tonne giants could kill a lion with a single kick.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.05,0:05:19.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,狮群很少会去叨扰如此棘手的猎物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Lions seldom tackle such formidable prey...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.67,0:05:27.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但没有食物充饥  狮群已寸步难行\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}...but this pride can't go on much longer without food.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.85,0:05:59.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为了猎杀成功\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The whole pride must work together as a team
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.25,0:06:00.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,整个狮群必须互相配合\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}if they're to succeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.53,0:06:32.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,两头母狮带头追捕\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Two lionesses lead the chase.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.91,0:06:36.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其他狮子奋起直追  切断猎物的逃生路线\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Others race to cut off possible escape routes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.73,0:06:58.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,长颈鹿的速度和耐力都强于狮群\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The giraffe has the speed and stamina to outrun the pride...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.87,0:07:03.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但它正被逐入敌人的陷阱\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}...but it's being chased into a trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.40,0:07:08.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,领头的母狮就在前面等待着\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Up ahead, the lead female waits.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.63,0:07:21.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,轮到她上场了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's now up to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.28,0:07:44.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,狮子的猎杀行动多以失败告终\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Most lion hunts end in failure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.96,0:07:51.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但沙漠种群的失败次数远比其他种群要多得多\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But no lions fail more often than those that live in the desert.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.87,0:07:59.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,狮群必须再次踏上寻找食物的征程\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Once again, the pride must continue their search.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.27,0:08:28.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沙漠地区偶尔也会降雨\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It does, sometimes, rain in the desert.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.66,0:08:33.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在美国西部地区\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Here, in the American West,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.77,0:08:37.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,暴风雨会带来灾难性的影响\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}storms can strike with devastating force.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.18,0:08:45.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,十个月的干旱以后\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}After ten months of drought,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.12,0:08:46.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,百万吨降水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}millions of tonnes of water
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.94,0:08:49.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在一小时内倾泻而下\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}are dumped on the land in under an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.95,0:09:43.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,数百万年来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Over millions of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.64,0:09:47.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,挟带着砂石的湍急洪水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}sand and gravel carried by the rampaging floods
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.24,0:09:50.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在坚硬的岩石上切割出凹槽\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}have carved channels through the solid rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.45,0:09:59.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,形成狭缝谷  深达四十六米\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Slot canyons, 150 feet deep.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.15,0:10:36.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一些地方的峡谷不断侵蚀扩张\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In some places, these canyons have widened
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.31,0:10:40.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最终形成桌状高地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}until the land between them is sculpted into tablelands
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.28,0:10:42.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,和高耸的石塔\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and isolated pinnacles,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.97,0:10:47.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是地球上最激动人心的自然奇观\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}some of the most dramatic landscapes on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.40,0:11:06.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雨季也许早已过去\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The rain may be long gone...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.16,0:11:10.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但沙漠里还是有水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}...but there is water here...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.99,0:11:16.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只是储存在沙生植物特化的组织当中\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}...locked away within the tissues of specialist desert plants.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.79,0:11:22.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,仙人掌是美国沙漠中独一无二的植物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Cacti are unique to American deserts.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.60,0:11:26.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们肥硕的茎干\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They all hoard water,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.63,0:11:29.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有储水功能\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}storing it in swollen stems
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.39,0:11:33.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,叶片特化成刺以防止水分散失\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and protecting it behind a barricade of spines.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.26,0:11:41.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这套策略成功地让它们主宰着这片沙漠\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They're so successful that they dominate these deserts.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.65,0:11:47.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但这片尖刺丛林也给居住在此的动物们\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But this forest of spikes can cause problems
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.34,0:11:49.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,带来了很多麻烦\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}for the animals that live here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.11,0:11:58.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一只栗翅鹰\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A Harris' Hawk.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.07,0:12:06.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它练就了在仙人掌林捕食的特殊技能\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It has developed special techniques for hunting amongst the cacti.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.98,0:12:14.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是地松鼠\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Ground squirrels.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.29,0:12:16.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,栗翅鹰的猎物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Prey.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.76,0:12:26.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当发现危险信号时\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At the first sign of danger
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.14,0:12:28.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,地松鼠们迅速躲进刺丛中避险\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they bolt for the safety of the thorns.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.89,0:12:42.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但栗翅鹰有法子逼它们出来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But the hawks have a tactic to flush them out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.44,0:12:49.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,栗翅鹰是唯一成群捕食的猛禽\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These are the only birds of prey that hunt in packs.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.12,0:12:53.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们编队飞行\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Flying in formation,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.42,0:12:56.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,将猎物驱赶到开阔地带\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they try to drive their quarry into the open.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.11,0:13:10.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但这只地松鼠按兵不动\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But this squirrel is staying put.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.42,0:13:20.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,栗翅鹰开始改变策略\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}So now the hawks continue the hunt...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.32,0:13:22.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,转为地面追击\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}...on foot.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.04,0:13:33.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们从四面八方逐渐逼近\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They're closing in from all sides.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.14,0:13:59.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很快封锁了所有的逃跑路线\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Soon, all escape routes are cut off.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.16,0:14:05.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,地松鼠陷入绝境\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The squirrel is trapped.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.48,0:14:20.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这片沙漠上的植物几乎都浑身是刺\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The spines that cover almost every plant in this desert
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.01,0:14:24.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们能为动物提供了庇护之所\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}can provide protection and shelter for many animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.09,0:14:38.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可这些尖刺上为什么挂着尸体\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}So, why should these spikes be hung with corpses?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.11,0:14:47.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如此可怕的场景究竟\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}What kind of creature could be responsible
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.51,0:14:50.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是谁的手笔呢\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}for creating such a gruesome scene?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.88,0:15:03.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这片沙漠里有一位神秘杀手\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There's a mysterious killer at work in this desert.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.44,0:15:13.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一只伯劳鸟\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's a butcherbird.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.12,0:15:18.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就像屠夫用钩子挂肉\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This little songbird uses the spines
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.38,0:15:20.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这只小型鸣禽利用这些刺\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}as a butcher uses his hook...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.05,0:15:24.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,将肢解完的食物悬挂起来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}to hold its prey as it dismembers it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.82,0:15:39.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,幼鸟们嗷嗷待哺  叶刺就像是食品储藏柜\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And with chicks to feed, he also uses the spines as a larder.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.47,0:15:48.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他已经储备了好几个星期\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}He's been stocking it for weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.52,0:15:55.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把猎物挂起来可以防止地面的食腐动物来争抢\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Hanging his prey out of the reach of scavengers on the ground
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.25,0:15:59.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以确保刚出生的幼鸟不会挨饿\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}ensures that his newly hatched young will never go hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.56,0:16:02.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为了让好时光持续更久点\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}An ingenious solution
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.37,0:16:06.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这的确是个巧妙的策略\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}to making the good times last in the desert...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.02,0:16:10.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,虽然有点毛骨悚然\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}...if a little macabre.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.33,0:16:22.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有的荒漠十分贫瘠\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Some deserts are so arid,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.73,0:16:26.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看似寸草不生\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they appear totally devoid of all vegetation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.31,0:16:34.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但即使是这种地方也能在几天之内焕然新生\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Yet even these landscapes can be transformed in a matter of days.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.76,0:16:50.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,秘鲁荒漠是世界上最干燥的地方之一\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The deserts of Peru are amongst the driest in the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.27,0:16:54.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,休眠了几个月的植被  只要遇到一点点水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but just add a little water and plants that have lain dormant for months
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.83,0:16:57.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,便可立即恢复生机\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}will burst into life.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.73,0:17:17.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当沙漠突然变为绿洲\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And when a desert suddenly turns green,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.69,0:17:20.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,即使看似最荒凉的地方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}even the most seemingly desolate
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.73,0:17:23.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也能变得生机勃勃\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}can become a land of opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.31,0:17:40.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有什么生物能比蝗虫更早或更轰动地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}No creature exploits the greening of a desert more quickly
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.15,0:17:43.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,发现这抹绿意\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}or more dramatically than a locust.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.29,0:17:54.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,马达加斯加干旱的西南部\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Madagascar's arid south-west
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.71,0:17:57.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,迎来了近几年最大的降雨\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}has received its highest rainfall in years.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.15,0:18:06.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,蝗虫大军正大步行进\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Now, an army is on the march,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.83,0:18:10.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,追寻着新生嫩芽的香气\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}attracted by the smell of newly sprouting grass.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.64,0:18:25.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,蝗虫通常独居\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Locusts are normally solitary creatures,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.25,0:18:27.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但当食物突然充足之时\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but when food becomes suddenly plentiful
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.83,0:18:31.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们便聚集成群  以势不可挡的气势\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they come together into an unstoppable force
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.34,0:18:34.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,吞噬沿途所有的植物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that devours everything in its path.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.11,0:18:57.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而这巨大的灾难正愈演愈烈\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But this devastation is about to get a lot worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.82,0:19:13.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,蝗虫正在变态为有翅的成虫\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The locusts now transform into winged adults,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.01,0:19:17.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,由于生长环境良好\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and with conditions as good as this,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.14,0:19:20.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们发育的速度达到平时的三倍\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they do so three times faster than normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.98,0:19:25.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在到了食欲最旺盛的时候\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Now they are at their most voracious...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.48,0:19:29.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有了翅膀  它们就能飞行\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and with wings, they can take to the skies.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.84,0:20:00.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一旦上天  蝗虫每天可以飞行九十六公里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Once airborne, the locusts can travel over 60 miles a day
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.48,0:20:03.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去寻找新的觅食区\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}in their search for new feeding grounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.50,0:20:22.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如此大规模的超级蝗群也许十年才出现一次\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A super swarm of this scale may only appear once in a decade.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.60,0:20:27.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个蝗群遍布五百一十八平方公里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This one extends over 200 square miles
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.11,0:20:30.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,共有数十亿只蝗虫\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and contains several billion individuals.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.84,0:20:36.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每天能吃掉四万吨食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Between them, they will devour 40,000 tonnes of food in a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.79,0:21:18.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,蝗灾吞噬植被的速度和彻底性\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Nothing can strip a land of its vegetation with such speed
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.15,0:21:21.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有任何事物能与之比肩\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and thoroughness as a plague of locusts.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.49,0:21:28.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当食物消耗殆尽时  蝗虫大军就会灭亡\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}When the food eventually runs out, the whole army will die...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.74,0:21:32.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但不等它们寂灭下来  世界早已一片狼藉\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but not before it's devastated the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.99,0:21:50.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有植被固定土壤\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}With no plants to bind them,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.37,0:21:54.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,稀薄的土层很快就会变成沙尘  被风吹走\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}thin soils soon turn to dust and blow away.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.45,0:22:06.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如今  这片不毛之地只能任由自然力量摆布\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Now, these barren lands are left to the mercy of the elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.76,0:22:28.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,烈日炙烤加之风沙侵袭\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Scorched by the sun and scoured by windblown sand,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.26,0:22:34.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沙漠岩石形成了奇异非凡的景致\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}desert rock is shaped into strange, otherworldly landscapes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.06,0:22:44.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这片岩质沙漠或许看似美好\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These rocky deserts may have a beguiling beauty,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.35,0:22:49.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但这里如此荒芜  极少生物能够适应\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but when they become this barren, very little life can endure.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.47,0:23:00.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,动物们想要在最严苛的环境里活下来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}For many animals, the only way to survive the most hostile times
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.96,0:23:02.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就必须不断迁移\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}is to keep moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.25,0:23:14.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,喀拉哈里沙漠短暂的雨季已被旱季替代\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In the Kalahari, brief rains have given way to the dry season.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.81,0:23:19.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,食物和水愈发稀缺\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Food and water are becoming increasingly scarce.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.21,0:23:23.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这群斑马是时候离开了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}For these zebra, it's time to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.33,0:23:40.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,斑马的迁移距离称霸\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They're setting off on the longest overland migration
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.98,0:23:43.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所有非洲哺乳动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}made by any mammal in Africa,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.60,0:23:47.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嗅着远方雨水的味道不断前进\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}marching towards the scent of distant rains.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.08,0:23:53.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,随着干旱加剧\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As drought intensifies,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.50,0:23:57.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沙漠象也必须踏上旅途\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}desert-living elephants must also undertake long journeys
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.01,0:23:58.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,寻找水源\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}in search of water.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.93,0:24:23.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,年长的母象能记住哪些地方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The older females can remember where,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.57,0:24:27.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,即使在极端干旱的季节也会有水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}even in times of extreme drought, there may still be water
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.85,0:24:31.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有时她能把象群带领到\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and sometimes lead the herd to a water hole
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.55,0:24:34.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,数十年前去过的水坑\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they may not have visited for decades.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.45,0:25:09.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这群斑马即将结束旅程\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These zebra are almost at the end of their journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.64,0:25:19.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里就是它们的目的地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is what they've been heading for...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.28,0:25:25.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一个珍贵的水坑\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}...A rare water hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.69,0:25:39.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沙漠里的大部分水坑都转瞬即逝\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In deserts, most water holes are short lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.40,0:25:41.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们在雨后出现\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They appear after rains,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.07,0:25:43.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但以几乎同样的速度消失\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but then vanish almost as quickly as they came.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.30,0:25:54.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,动物长途跋涉来到这里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Animals have come here from many miles around.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.68,0:26:04.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但在此地逗留可能会有危险\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Yet this can be a dangerous place in which to linger.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.91,0:26:16.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,离水坑九十六公里远的沙漠中心\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}60 miles away, in the heart of the desert,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.16,0:26:18.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沙鸡的雏鸟正在孵化\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}sandgrouse chicks are hatching.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.70,0:26:22.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们待在这里比较安全\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's safer for them to be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.97,0:26:30.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是离水源那么远  也有很大风险\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But being so distant from water is a gamble.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.22,0:26:37.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只有母亲在帮他们遮挡太阳\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}With only their mother to shield them from the sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.05,0:26:41.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果没有水喝  雏鸟会在数小时内曝晒而死\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}if they get nothing to drink, they will be dead within hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.96,0:26:52.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,唯一的希望寄托在父亲身上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Their only hope is their father.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.06,0:27:00.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每天早上  他都要往返飞行一百九十三公里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Every morning he makes the 120-mile round trip
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.32,0:27:02.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为家人带水回来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}to get water for the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.12,0:27:09.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沙鸡从四面八方飞来这片绿洲\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Grouse from all over the desert visit this oasis,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.77,0:27:12.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在这里集结成群\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}arriving together in large flocks,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.18,0:27:15.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这十分重要\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and that is important.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.67,0:27:21.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,数量越多越安全\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There's safety in numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.47,0:27:38.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雄沙鸡抓紧时间喝了口水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The male snatches a drink,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.01,0:27:42.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但他还要给雏鸟们带水回去\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but he also needs to collect water for his chicks.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.62,0:27:46.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他胸前特化的羽毛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Using specially adapted breast feathers,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.07,0:27:48.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可以像海绵一样吸收大量的水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}he can soak up water like a sponge.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.01,0:27:53.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过这需要时间  而他已身陷危险\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But it takes time, and he is in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.63,0:28:02.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,苍鹰\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Goshawk.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.84,0:28:22.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沙鸡是他们的主要猎物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Sandgrouse here are their main prey.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.84,0:28:33.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,日复一日  雄沙鸡都要冒着生命危险\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Again and again, the male sandgrouse risk their lives
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.64,0:28:36.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来给雏鸟采水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}in order to collect water for their chicks.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.36,0:29:02.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这就是沙鸡巢离水坑如此远的原因\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is why sandgrouse nest so far from water holes.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.65,0:29:30.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,终于  他吸足了水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At last, he's soaked up as much as he can.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.09,0:29:35.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,带着自身体重四分之一的水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Carrying a quarter of his body weight in water,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.28,0:29:38.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他开始漫长的归家旅程\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}he can now set off on the long journey home.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.51,0:30:09.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到家了  时间刚刚好\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}He's back, and just in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.76,0:30:14.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雏鸟可以喝上第一口水了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}He can give the chicks their first ever drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.83,0:30:26.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但在未来两个月  他依然每天都要\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But he will have to undertake this perilous journey every day
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.18,0:30:27.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,踏上这段危险的征程\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}for the next two months
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.99,0:30:30.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,直到雏鸟长大\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}until his chicks can finally make the flight
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.53,0:30:33.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,能独自飞到水坑\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}to the water hole for themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.72,0:30:51.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,美国西部内华达州沙漠的七月\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's July in the deserts of Nevada in the western United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.45,0:30:54.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是一年中最炎热的时候\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The hottest time of the year.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.95,0:31:13.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一群群美洲野马聚集在\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Bands of wild horses, mustang, are converging on
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.14,0:31:16.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,方圆几公里内仅存的水塘边\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}one of the last remaining water holes for miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.08,0:31:25.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,水不仅能用来喝\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Now, water not only offers them the chance to drink,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.39,0:31:28.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还能借此获得权力\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}it can also bring power.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.76,0:31:35.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果一头公马能够控制饮水权\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}If a stallion can control access to water,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.12,0:31:38.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,便拥有与群中所有母马交配的权利\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}he will have secured mating rights to the entire herd.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.25,0:31:43.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以公马们会试图独占水塘\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}So stallions try to dominate these pools,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.31,0:31:46.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,赶走所有想要靠近的竞争对手\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}fighting off rivals who venture too close.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.73,0:32:01.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一位不速之客\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A stranger.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.92,0:32:05.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他跋涉了十六公里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}He's travelled ten miles to be here
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.23,0:32:08.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为他所在地方的水源已经完全干涸\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}because the pools where he's come from have already dried up.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.17,0:32:15.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他身后跟着一群母马\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}With him come his females.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.95,0:32:21.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果他无法提供水源  她们都会离开\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}If he can't provide them with water, they will leave him
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.04,0:32:24.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,跟这匹已经占有水池的白马在一起\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}for the white stallion who already dominates this pool.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.18,0:32:38.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他必须选择战斗\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}So, he will have to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.43,0:33:43.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这一战至关重要\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There is everything to lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.89,0:33:47.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,若是断了腿  或是碎了下巴\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A broken leg or a shattered jaw
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.13,0:33:50.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就意味着死前将饱受折磨\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}would mean a slow and painful death.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.68,0:34:15.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没踢中  一切都结束了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A missed kick, and it's all over.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.39,0:34:19.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,新来的马取得了胜利\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The new arrival has won...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.81,0:34:25.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他所获得的奖赏不只是可以喝水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and his prize is more than just the chance to drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.26,0:34:29.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他为马群提供了水源  与此同时\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}He has provided for his herd, and in the process,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.62,0:34:31.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抢走了竞争对手的后宫\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}stolen his rival's females.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.93,0:34:36.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,白马的统治已经结束\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The white stallion's rule is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.51,0:34:49.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沙漠中不仅水源稀缺\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Desert life is not only shaped by the scarcity of water,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.36,0:34:54.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,更有炎炎烈日的残酷炙烤\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but also by the relentless power of the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.99,0:35:03.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,地球上的最高温度记录\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The highest temperatures on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.23,0:35:06.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,全部出现于沙漠中\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}have all been recorded in its deserts.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.22,0:35:21.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,气候变化让这里的温度\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Changes in the climate mean temperatures here
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.44,0:35:24.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,涨幅和速度都超过全球平均值\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}are rising more than the global average,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.26,0:35:28.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,随着温度升高  沙漠也在不断扩散\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and as deserts heat up, they are also expanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.40,0:35:35.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每年都有近十三万平方公里的草地和农田\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Every year, a further 50,000 square miles of grass and farmland
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.71,0:35:39.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,变成了贫瘠干涸的尘土沙石\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}are turning into barren stretches of dust and rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.23,0:35:46.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一天中最热之时\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In the heat of the day,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.68,0:35:50.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沙漠地表温度可达七十一摄氏度\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}surface temperatures can reach 160 degrees,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.19,0:35:54.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大多数生物都无法忍受\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}far too hot to handle for most.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.35,0:36:00.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但这只铲吻蜥蜴却可以\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But not for this shovel-snouted lizard.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.73,0:36:07.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它将四肢轮流抬起\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Raising its feet off the ground in turn...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.88,0:36:13.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,短暂降温一下\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}...enables each to briefly cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.79,0:36:23.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可即便是这位耐热性极强的沙漠舞者\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But even this dancing desert specialist
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.03,0:36:25.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也无法长时间忍受高温\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}can't stand the heat for long.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.12,0:36:36.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一个办法是寻找阴凉\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}One option is to find shade.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.53,0:36:46.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沙丘草是这里唯一的植物  近乎无荫可寻\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Dune grass, the only vegetation here, provides virtually none,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.99,0:36:49.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但仅仅是沙子表面下几厘米处\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but just an inch beneath the surface of the sand,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.97,0:36:52.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,温度都要低上几度\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}it is several degrees cooler.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.39,0:37:05.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为躲避难耐的高温  沙漠动物有了自己的节奏\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Avoiding the extreme heat imposes a rhythm on desert life.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.27,0:37:12.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,许多动物都选择了最简单的解决方案...\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And many animals here choose the simplest option of all...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.26,0:37:16.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,白天隐匿在各处\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}staying hidden all day,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.14,0:37:20.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只在凉爽的夜晚外出活动\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and only venturing out in the cool of the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.39,0:37:34.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,夜幕降临  动物纷纷从各处冒出\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As darkness falls, animals appear from seemingly nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.71,0:37:44.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而这之中  必然存在\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And, among them, inevitably,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.68,0:37:47.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,猎食者\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}are hunters.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.57,0:38:05.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其中最贪婪的夜间捕食者\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}One of the most voracious nocturnal predators
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.94,0:38:09.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也最难寻觅它们的踪迹\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}is also one of the hardest to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.07,0:38:13.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个神秘的生物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This mysterious creature
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.94,0:38:17.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,鲜少出现在沙丘表面\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}hardly ever appears on the surface of the dunes.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.10,0:38:28.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但沙子的移动  却泄露了它的行踪\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But there are signs on the sand that can give it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.40,0:38:43.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它只生活在\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It lives only here,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.66,0:38:47.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沙粒干燥光滑的地区\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}where the sand grains are so perfectly dry and polished,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.17,0:38:49.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让它们可以如流水般行动自如\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that they flow almost like water.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.27,0:38:55.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它的体型还没有乒乓球大\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's no bigger than a ping-pong ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.45,0:39:02.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一只金毛鼹鼠\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A golden mole.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.03,0:39:04.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它的视力已完全退化\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's totally blind,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.82,0:39:08.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但地下本来也没有什么可看的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but there's nothing to see underground anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.16,0:39:17.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,取而代之的是它极佳的听觉\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Instead, it has superb hearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.64,0:39:23.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它的头犹如扩音器\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Its entire head acts as an amplifier
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.40,0:39:26.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,能够捕捉通过沙子传来的振动\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that picks up vibrations through the sand,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.42,0:39:29.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以  为了定位沙丘表面上的猎物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so, to locate prey on the surface of the dune,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.65,0:39:34.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它反而矛盾地将脸埋进沙子里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}it has, paradoxically, to thrust its face into the dune.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.20,0:39:44.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,白蚁\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Termites.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.35,0:39:47.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,双目失明自然不太好捉\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Not easy to catch when you're blind.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.04,0:39:55.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最好还是切换成隐身模式\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Far better to go into stealth mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.59,0:39:58.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一旦潜入沙中\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Once below the sand,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.40,0:40:01.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,金毛鼹鼠可以感知微弱的震动\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}it can detect the slightest movement...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.53,0:40:08.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让它能发动精准袭击\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}allowing it to strike with pinpoint accuracy.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.74,0:40:20.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大多数时候是这样\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Well, most of the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.73,0:40:35.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们一晚可以行进1.1公里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They can travel two thirds of a mile a night
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.53,0:40:37.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来寻找晚餐\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}in search of its dinner...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.88,0:40:44.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在  它刚刚发现了自己的主菜\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and right now, it has just detected its main course.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.93,0:40:50.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,难怪它有时候被称作“沙丘之鲨”\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Little wonder it's sometimes called "The shark of the dunes".
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.83,0:41:03.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,食物在沙漠中非常稀缺  即便是在夜晚\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Food can be so scarce in the desert that, even at night,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.35,0:41:07.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,动物们也无权挑剔自己的饮食\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}animals can't afford to be choosy about what they eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.66,0:41:16.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在以色列的内盖夫沙漠\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Israel's Negev desert.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.73,0:41:30.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,中东尖耳蝠  沙漠中的长耳蝙蝠  正在捕猎\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Otonycteris, the desert long-eared bat, is on the hunt.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.02,0:41:38.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大多数蝙蝠在飞行中捕捉飞虫\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Most bats catch flying insects on the wing,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.61,0:41:40.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但在沙漠中飞虫数量极少\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but there are so few of these in the desert
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.91,0:41:43.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这只蝙蝠必须另寻他路\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that this bat must do things differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.73,0:41:50.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它必须在地面捕猎\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It has to hunt on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.68,0:42:01.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但真正让它与众不同的是它的猎物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But what really sets it apart is what it's hunting...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.98,0:42:12.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一只以色列金蝎\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A deathstalker scorpion.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.61,0:42:18.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这种蝎子的毒液足以毒死一个人\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The venom of this species is potent enough to kill a human.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.85,0:42:24.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,捕捉毒蝎对于仅有十四克重的蝙蝠来说近乎疯狂\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Tackling it seems madness for a bat weighing just half an ounce.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.98,0:42:30.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,周围一片漆黑\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In the pitch-black,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.51,0:42:33.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,猎食者和猎物都丧失了视力\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}both predator and prey are effectively blind,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.37,0:42:36.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是蝎子有一项优势\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but the scorpion has one advantage...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.95,0:42:39.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他能够通过沙子的振动\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}he can sense the approach of the bat
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.42,0:42:42.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,感知到蝙蝠的靠近\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}through vibrations in the sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.36,0:42:50.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尖耳蝠则要完全依靠自己的听觉\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Otonycteris must rely entirely on its hearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.96,0:42:54.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果蝎子不动  它就无法感知其位置\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}If the scorpion doesn't move, it won't know it's there.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.88,0:43:11.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,战斗打响了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The battle is on.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.21,0:43:18.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,凭借强大的双钳和一根毒刺\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Armed with crushing pincers and a sting loaded with venom,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.29,0:43:21.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这只毒蝎是一个危险的对手\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}this scorpion is a dangerous opponent.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.98,0:43:37.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,蝙蝠脑袋遭到一记猛刺\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A direct strike on the head.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.08,0:43:41.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,战斗结束了吗\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Is it all over?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.41,0:43:47.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对这只蝙蝠来说并没有\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Not for this bat.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.24,0:44:07.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尖耳蝠显然对毒液有一定的免疫\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Otonycteris clearly has some immunity to the venom,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.51,0:44:12.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但连续的猛刺给它带来了难言的剧痛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but repeated stings must still be extraordinarily painful.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.03,0:44:22.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果这只蝙蝠不想挨饿\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And if the bat is not to go hungry,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.14,0:44:26.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它必须在日出之前再抓住三只蝎子\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}it must catch another three scorpions before sunrise.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.26,0:44:58.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沙漠动物进化出了非凡的策略\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Desert animals have developed remarkable strategies
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.95,0:45:02.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来充分利用难得的良机\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}to make the most of the rare opportunities that come their way.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.97,0:45:08.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,虽然有些沙漠也许数年都不会下雨\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Although some deserts may not see rain for several years,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.67,0:45:12.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但大多数都会以各种形式储存少量的水分\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}most will hold a little water in one form or another.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.56,0:45:17.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,诀窍在于如何获取水分\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The trick is simply knowing how to reach it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.93,0:45:29.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,破晓时分  纳米布沙漠的沙丘上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Dawn in the dunes of the Namib,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.31,0:45:31.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,神奇的现象正在发生\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and something magical is happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.32,0:45:54.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大西洋沿岸上空的湿空气\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Moist air lying over the neighbouring Atlantic
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.71,0:45:57.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,冷却并被吹至内陆\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}is cooled and blown inland,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.39,0:46:01.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,形成雾堤  笼罩沙漠\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}forming fog banks that shroud the desert in mist.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.91,0:46:13.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些珍贵的水汽诱人地弥漫在沙丘顶部\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This precious moisture lies tantalisingly out of reach
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.60,0:46:17.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,难以触及  而且不会久留\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}at the top of the dunes, and it won't last long.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.91,0:46:22.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,太阳升起数小时后就会被烤干\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It'll be burnt off by the sun just hours after it rises.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.27,0:46:41.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拟步甲狂奔至沙丘顶部\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Darkling beetles race to the top of the dunes
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.65,0:46:44.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要赶在薄雾消失之前吸收水分\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}to reach the fog before it vanishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.70,0:46:57.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,纳米布的沙丘有些高达三百米\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Some of the Namib's dunes are 1,000 feet high,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.38,0:47:00.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,堪称世界之最\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the tallest in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.84,0:47:05.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对于拇指盖大小的甲虫来说  攀爬距离相当于\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}For a beetle no larger than a thumbnail, this is the equivalent
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.83,0:47:09.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人类攀爬一座比珠穆朗玛峰高两倍的沙丘\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}of us climbing a dune twice the height of Everest.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.25,0:47:18.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但更令人印象深刻的是它接下来的举动\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But even more impressive is what it does next.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.11,0:47:26.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,身体正直  迎面朝风\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Standing perfectly still, facing into the wind,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.55,0:47:29.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,甲虫倒立在沙丘上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the beetle does a headstand.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.55,0:47:35.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,薄雾开始在它身上凝结成水滴\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Fog begins to condense on its body.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.00,0:47:41.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,鞘翅上的小凸起\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Microscopic bumps on its wing cases
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.58,0:47:45.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,将水引到通向嘴部的一个小沟渠里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}direct the water to grooves that channel it towards the mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.19,0:47:53.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在回到背风坡上之前\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Before returning down the slip face,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.78,0:47:56.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它要喝下百分之四十体重的水分\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}it will drink 40% of its body weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.97,0:48:03.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这只小甲虫学会了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This little beetle has learned
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.98,0:48:06.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如何在地球上最干燥的地方之一\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}how to conjure water out of the air
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.50,0:48:10.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从空气中变出水来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}in one of the driest places on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.18,0:48:17.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然而它并非沙丘顶部唯一的访客\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And it's not alone on the top of the dunes.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.39,0:48:27.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,蹼趾虎也采用了相似的办法\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Web-footed geckos use a similar trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.81,0:48:42.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,肯定少有动物跋涉更远的距离去获取水分\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Surely, few animals go to greater lengths to get a drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.09,0:49:05.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不幸的是  纳米比亚变色龙知道在薄雾弥漫的早晨\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Unfortunately, Namaqua chameleons know that on foggy mornings,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.36,0:49:07.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从沙丘上下来的甲虫\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the beetles coming down the dunes
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.79,0:49:10.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,会比上去的更多汁\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}are juicier than those going up.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.41,0:49:25.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在这样一个水资源完全匮乏的世界\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The diversity of life that thrives in a world
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.63,0:49:29.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,生物多样性如此之高  确实令人惊叹\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}almost totally devoid of water is truly remarkable.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.46,0:49:34.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在沙漠中成功存活\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Success in the desert
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.03,0:49:38.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,依靠的是数百万年进化而来的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}depends on an extraordinary variety of survival strategies
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.20,0:49:40.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,非凡多样的生存策略\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that have evolved over millions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.21,0:49:45.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我们的地球正遭受着变故\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But our planet is changing.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.82,0:49:52.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,世界沙漠的面积在扩大  温度更高  更加干燥\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The world's deserts are growing bigger, hotter and drier,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.05,0:49:56.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且在以史无前例的速度变化着\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and they're doing so faster than ever before.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.97,0:50:03.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沙漠生命在未来如何存活  依旧有待观察\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}How life will cope here in the future remains to be seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.29,0:50:15.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,下一集  我们将探访地球上的平原\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Next time, we journey to the world's great plains,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.69,0:50:22.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,壮观的野生动物群在那里适应着极端的变化\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}where spectacular gatherings of wildlife cope with extreme change...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.20,0:50:28.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而奇妙的生物  有着意想不到的生存方式\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}...and surprising creatures survive in unexpected ways.

